Program: Discovery
Title: Cosmic Questions - Part Two
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrxd8
Last Broadcast Date: 29 April 1999
The second in a series looking at the dawn of time and space. An examination of the mysteries of the cosmos and the Big Bang theory, examining the framework and going deeper to ask not only 'what', 'how", 'when' but more importantly 'why' questions, uniting scientific and theological issues. The American Association for the Advancement of Science (AAAS) recently held a conference at the Smithsonian Institute entitled 'Cosmic Questions', examining the dawn of time in terms of both religion and science. Show less